<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.263388>
    dc:description "PLATE 87. Fenimorea moseri (Dall, 1889). Upper panel. Figs. 1 – 2: lectotype St. Martin's Reef, Hernando Co., W Florida (USNM 86925). Fig. 1: ventral, lateral & dorsal views; Fig. 2: apical view, V = varix, L = edge of outer lip; Fig. 3: paralectotype, Sarasota Bay, Sarasota Co., W Florida (USNM 27638); Fig. 4: paralectotype, off Cape Hatteras, North Carolina (USNM 93611). Lower panel. Fig. 5: holotype, Neodrillia blacki Petuch, 1987, E shore, Middle Torch Key, Florida Keys (AMNH 308071); Figs. 6 – 7: E end of Middle Torch Key, Florida Bay, Florida Keys (author’s coll.); Figs. 8 – 9: Middle Torch Key, Bay side, Florida Keys (UF 123002); Fig. 10: holotype, Fenimorea moseri brunnescens Rehder, 1943, off Fort Walton, Okaloosa Co., W Florida (USNM 517055); Fig. 11: off E Pass, Destin, Okaloosa Co., W Florida (UF 242587); Fig. 12: 225 ° off Panama City, Bay Co. W Florida (UF 156501); Fig. 13 – 14: Fort Walton Bay, Okaloosa Co., W Florida (UF 59986)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/263388/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.263389>
    dc:description "PLATE 88. Fenimorea moseri (Dall, 1889). Figs. 1 – 2: W of John Sawyer Bank, Marathon, Florida Keys (EFG 11601); Fig. 3: near John Sawyer Bank, Marathon, Florida Keys (EFG 21900); Fig. 4: Little Torch Key, Florida Keys (DMNH 197563); Fig. 5: Bay side, Middle Torch Key, Florida Keys (UF 123002); Fig. 6: off Anclote Key, Pasco Co., W Florida (ANSP 314402); Fig. 7: S of Cape Eleuthera harbor, Eleuthera, Bahama Is. (author’s coll.); Fig. 8: off St. Johns Pass, Pinellas Co., W Florida (author’s coll.); Figs. 9, 11: off Sanibel I., Lee Co., W. Florida (UF 155642); Fig. 10: WSW of Sanibel I., Lee Co., W Florida (author’s coll.); Figs. 12 – 13: W of Boca Grande, Lee Co., W Florida (EFG 11577); Figs. 14 – 15: S of Cape Eleuthera harbor, Eleuthera, Bahama Is. (author’s coll.); Figs. 16 – 17: Fort Walton Bay, Okaloosa Co., W Florida (UF 59986); Figs. 18 – 21: WSW of Triángulos Reef, Campeche Bank, Mexico (EFG 26524)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/263389/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

